  "texts": [
    "Results CircDA performanceThe main purpose of our study is to build a predictor with high accuracy in predicting diseases associated with circRNA molecules.We first optimize the learning rate (LR) according to the AUROC and AUPR.",
    "First of all, based on experience, we analyze the effect of three LR schemes (Adam, step size-based decay, linear learning rate decay) and fixed LRs (0.002, 0.0005).",
    "In Fig. 2A, B, the AUROC values obtained by the Adam method are 0.9716, 0.9426, 0.9465, and 0.9703, and AUPR values are significantly better than those of the other schemes.",
    "Therefore, Adam is chosen to be the LR of the model, and its initial value is empirically set to 0.001.Furthermore, the hyperparameters α and β in the loss function Eqs.",
    "(11 and 12) lead to changes in performance."
  ],
